    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-05-13T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-05-13T20:00:00-05:00" n="1082"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1082">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">816.00/1411a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in El Salvador</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Thurston</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-05-13T21:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 13, 1944—9 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>141. You are authorized to acknowledge receipt on May 16 in appropriate terms of
                    the note transcribed in your telegram no. 164 of May 12, thereby showing the
                    purpose of this Government to continue normal diplomatic relations with the
                    incoming Salvadoran administration. A circular telegram is being addressed to
                    the missions in <pb facs="1115" n="1101" xml:id="pg_1101"/> the other American
                        Republics<note n="30" xml:id="d1082fn30">Addressed on May 13 to diplomatic
                        representatives in all the American Republics except Bolivia, Argentina, and
                        El Salvador; not printed.</note> informing them of this and instructing them
                    to inform the governments to which they are accredited of this Government’s
                    intention.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
